In compliance with the presidential directive that all the Service Chiefs relocate to the Theatre of the war against insurgency, the Chief of Defence Staff, Gen Abayomi Gabriel Olanisakin, Chief of Army Staff, Lt-Gen Tukur Yusuf Burutai, Chief of Air Staff, Air Marshal Sadiq Abubakar and Chief of Naval Staff, Vice Admiral Ibok Ette Ibas along with the Director General Of the State Security Services, Lawan Daura have arrived Maiduguri. On their arrival at the command and control Centre of the Theatre Command of operation Lafiya Dole Theartre Command yesterday, the Security Chiefs along with the Theatre Commander of operation Lafiya Dole , Maj Gen Rogers Nicholas held a closed door meeting 2pm and 5pm. Addressing newsmen immediately after the meeting , the Defence Spokesman, Brig Gen John Agim  said the closed door meeting reviewed the entire operations of the Operation Lafiya dole with the sole aim of restrategizing the whole operations with a view to rescue the Dapchi GGSTC schoolgirls and the remaining Chibok GGSS schoolgirls  as well as ending the nine years Boko Haram insurgency. He, however, said the CDS expressed dismay over some media reports that the Nigerian military have engaged the services of fishermen and farmers in some parts of the country in the fight against Boko Haram insurgency and the search for the missing Schoolgirls.